NAME
     add-library - adds one or  more  library  archive  files  to
     GlassFish Server

SYNOPSIS
     add-library [--help] [--type={common|ext|app}] [--upload={false|true}]
     [--target target]
     library-file-path [library-file-path ... ]

DESCRIPTION
     The add-library subcommand adds one or more library  archive
     files to GlassFish Server.

     The --type option specifies the library type and the GlassF-
     ish Server directory to which the library is added.

     The --target option specifies the target to  which  you  are
     adding  the  libraries. If this option specifies the domain,
     the libraries are added only to  the  configuration  of  the
     domain administration server (DAS). If this option specifies
     any other target, the libraries are added to the  configura-
     tion  of  the  DAS and references are added to the libraries
     from the specified target.

     The library-file-path operand is the path to  the  JAR  file
     that  contains  the library to be added. To specify multiple
     libraries, specify multiple paths separated by spaces.

     Note

     The library archive file is added to the  DAS.  To  add  the
     libraries  to  other server instances, synchronize them with
     the DAS by restarting them.

     This Note will no longer be valid when the  --target  option
     is implemented.

     This subcommand is supported in remote mode only.

OPTIONS
     --help , -?
          Displays the help text for the subcommand.

     --type
          Specifies the library type  and  the  GlassFish  Server
          directory  to  which the library is added. Valid values
          are as follows:

          common
               Adds the library files to the Common class  loader
               directory, domain-dir/lib. This is the default.

