          ext  Adds the library files to the Java optional  pack-
               age directory, domain-dir/lib/ext.

          app  Adds the library files to the application-specific
               class loader directory, domain-dir/lib/applibs.

     For  more  information  about  these  directories,  seeClass
     Loaders  in  Oracle GlassFish Server Application Development
     Guide .

     --upload
          Specifies whether the subcommand uploads  the  file  to
          the  DAS.  In most situations, this option can be omit-
          ted.

          Valid values are as follows:

          false
               The  subcommand  does  not  upload  the  file  and
               attempts  to access the file through the specified
               file name. If the DAS cannot access the file,  the
               subcommand fails.

               For example, the DAS might be running  as  a  dif-
               ferent  user than the administration user and does
               not have read access to the file. In  this  situa-
               tion,  the subcommand fails if the --upload option
               is false.

          true The subcommand uploads the file to  the  DAS  over
               the network connection.

     The default value depends on whether the DAS is on the  host
     where the subcommand is run or is on a remote host.

          o If the DAS is on the host  where  the  subcommand  is
            run, the default is false.

          o If the DAS is on a remote host, the default is true.

     If  a  directory  filepath  is  specified,  this  option  is
     ignored.

     --target
          Specifies the  target  to  which  you  are  adding  the
          libraries. Valid values are as follows:

          server
               Adds the libraries to the default server  instance

